    "content": "<p><em>I dedicate this work to</em></p><p><em>Al-Sayyid al-Sharīf al-Shaykh al-Rabbānī</em></p><p><em>‘Abd-al-Shakūr ibn-Ibrāhīm ibn-Yūsuf ibn-‘Abd-al-Salām ibn-Zayn-al-‘Ābidīn </em></p><p><em>al-Ḥasanī al-Jīlānī al-Qādirī (d. 1404/1984)</em></p><p>God says in the Qur’ān: “As for the Blessings of your Lord [upon you], proclaim [them gratefully]!” And the Prophet said: “Whoever does not give thanks to People, does not give thanks to God.” In the West, we say: “Many hands make light work.” I am both very obliged and tremendously happy to express great thanks to all those many Brothers and Sisters who have been so generous in making this book possible—both through excellent counsel, priceless advice, and strenuous collaboration. They are so many that I cannot do justice to them all, and many of them prefer not to be mentioned. I have, however, listed many of their names in the Web-Extension of this Syntopicon (1:3).</p><p>                                               Image 2:</p><p>                                   <em>Al-Sayyid ‘Abd-al-Shakūr</em></p><p><em>                                          </em>Image 3:</p><p>                                                    <strong>Wonder is the beginning of wisdom</strong><sup data-footnote=\"1\" data-footnote-key=\"web-extension-dedication:web-extension:1\" data-footnote-origin=\"web-extension\">1</sup>.<sup></sup></p><p>Place here a short biography about Sayyidi ‘Abd-al-Shakur and his family.</p>",
