        "markerKey": "web-extension-there-is-no-god-but-god-without-god-there-is-no-man:web-extension:9",
        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p><strong> Sir Muḥammad Iqbāl</strong> (d. 1357/1938) or ‘Allāma Muḥammad Iqbāl was one of the greatest poets of the fourteenth/twentieth century and wrote in both Urdu and Persian. He was trained as a barrister (lawyer) in British India and also excelled as a great thinker and philosopher. He is called the “Spiritual Father of Pakistan” in light of his strong support for the movement to create Pakistan as a Muslim homeland in Greater India. </p>",
        "sectionId": "web-extension-there-is-no-god-but-god-without-god-there-is-no-man"
