        "displayNumber": 18,
        "markerKey": "web-extension-there-is-no-god-but-god-without-god-there-is-no-man:web-extension:18",
        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> <strong>Ernest Burgmann</strong> (d. 1387/1967) or, more fully, Ernest Henry Burgmann, was a prominent Australian Bishop of the Church of England and an outspoken social activist. Throughout his life, however, he avoided joining any particular political party, while still remaining active in Australian politics. Burgmann expressed strong interests in and commitments to working-class issues. He was part of the Australian delegation to the United Nations Assembly in Paris in 1367/1948. During his life, Burgmann wrote prolifically on Biblical interpretation, social justice, and reform.  </p>",
        "sectionId": "web-extension-there-is-no-god-but-god-without-god-there-is-no-man"
