        "markerKey": "web-extension-islam-s-corrective-tradition-madhhab-al-tahqiq-the-school-of-verification:web-extension:51",
        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> Among the notable exceptions of Sunnī scholars who have a profound understanding of the Critical Tradition and its universality among Sunnīs and Shī‘īs, one can mention the noteworthy Iraqi Scholars of Baghdad—each of whom belong fully to the Mature Tradition, taught, and cultivated it: Al-Sayyid al-Shaykh Abū-al-Ḥasan Abū-al-Si‘d al-Rifā‘ī (d. 1407/1987), al-Sayyid al-Shaykh ‘Abd-al-Karīm al-Mudarris (d. 1426/2005), and the contemporary heir of the Tradition al-Sayyid al-Shaykh Quṣayy Abū-al-Si‘d al-Rifā‘ī (born 1386/1967). Among the Shī‘a, the same understanding of the universality of the Corrective Tradition has been espoused publicly by al-‘Allāma Ḥasanzāde al-Āmulī (d. 1442/2021) and the contemporary Grand Āyat-Allāh, al-Sayyid Kamāl al-Ḥusaynī al-Ḥaydarī (born 1375/1956).  </p>",
