        "markerKey": "web-extension-islam-s-corrective-tradition-madhhab-al-tahqiq-the-school-of-verification:web-extension:52",
        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> <strong>Mullā Maḥmūd al-Jaunpūrī </strong>(d. <strong>1062</strong>/1652) was an older contemporary of Mīr Dāmād. Al-Jaunpūrī is one of the earlier representatives of the Corrective Tradition in the Greater Indian Subcontinent, and he was the author of the famous Metaphysical work <em>The Dazzling Rising Sun </em>(<em>Al-Shams al-Bāzigha</em>). He died and is buried in Jaunpur. </p>",
        "sectionId": "web-extension-islam-s-corrective-tradition-madhhab-al-tahqiq-the-school-of-verification"
