        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> <strong>Mullā ‘Abd-al-Ḥakīm al-Siālkūtī </strong>(d. 1067/1657) hailed from Sialkot in the Punjab, which at the time was one of the great centers of learning in Mughal India. Al-Shaykh Aḥmad al-Sirhindī (d. 1034/1624) was among the many luminaries who studied in Sialkot under the aegis of Mullā ‘Abd-al-Ḥakīm al-Siālkūtī. He died and was buried in Sialkot. </p>",
